text: Anabura or Anaboura () was a town of ancient Pisidia, inhabited during Hellenistic, Roman, and Byzantine times. Its site is located near Enevre in Asiatic Turkey. ==References== Category:Populated places in Pisidia Category:Former populated places in Turkey Category:Roman towns and cities in Turkey Category:Populated places of the Byzantine Empire Category:History of Isparta Province Category:Şarkikaraağaç District
title: Anabura (Pisidia)
